author: Timothy Puko
title: Analysts See 61 Billion Cubic-Feet Add to U.S. Natural-Gas Inventories
text:
Analysts expect government data scheduled for release Thursday to show natural-gas inventories last week rose on par with their five-year average.
The U.S. Energy Information Administration is expected to report that storage levels grew by 61 billion cubic feet of gas during the week ended Aug. 21, according to the average forecast of 24...
